{"query": {"pages": {"31720290": {"lastrevid": 615236951, "pageid": 31720290, "canonicalurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Bierstedt", "title": "Robert Bierstedt", "editurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Robert_Bierstedt&action=edit", "length": 4129, "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "touched": "2015-03-21T12:13:36Z", "ns": 0, "fullurl": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Bierstedt", "revisions": [{"*": "<p><b>Robert Bierstedt</b> (1913\u20131998) was an <a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Sociology\" title=\"Sociology\">sociologist</a> who often wrote about sociological theory, culture, and constitutional law. He was a native of <a href=\"/wiki/Burlington,_Iowa\" title=\"Burlington, Iowa\">Burlington, Iowa</a> and graduated in philosophy from the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Iowa\" title=\"University of Iowa\">University of Iowa</a> in 1934. He received a master's degree in philosophy in 1935 and a doctorate in sociology in 1946 from <a href=\"/wiki/Columbia_University\" title=\"Columbia University\">Columbia University</a>.\n</p><p>He headed the department of sociology at <a href=\"/wiki/City_College_of_New_York\" title=\"City College of New York\">City College of New York</a> and at <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_University\" title=\"New York University\">New York University</a> before becoming emeritus professor of sociology at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Virginia\" title=\"University of Virginia\">University of Virginia</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> He was a student of the <a href=\"/wiki/Russian-American\" title=\"Russian-American\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Russian-American</a> sociologist <a href=\"/wiki/Pitirim_Sorokin\" title=\"Pitirim Sorokin\">Pitirim Sorokin</a> when he was a visiting graduate student at Harvard University during the 1930s.Bierstedt served as vice-president of the American Sociological Association when Sorokin was elected president. \n</p><p>Bierstedt was a longtime director of the <a href=\"/wiki/American_Civil_Liberties_Union\" title=\"American Civil Liberties Union\">American Civil Liberties Union</a>, serving as chairman of its academic freedom committee and the church-state committee in the 1960s and 1970s. In addition, he was a former director of the <a href=\"/wiki/American_Council_of_Learned_Societies\" title=\"American Council of Learned Societies\">American Council of Learned Societies</a>, a federation of scholarly groups focused on the humanities, and president of the <a href=\"/wiki/Eastern_Sociological_Society\" title=\"Eastern Sociological Society\">Eastern Sociological Society</a>. In his 1959 presidential address \"Sociology and Humane Learning\" to the Eastern Sociological Society he argued for the role of debate in sociology and the importance of what he referred to as the \"theoretic bias\" in interpreting social phenomena.\n</p><p>He also held Fulbright Senior Lectureships at <a href=\"/wiki/Edinburgh_University\" title=\"Edinburgh University\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Edinburgh University</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/London_School_of_Economics\" title=\"London School of Economics\">London School of Economics</a>.\n</p><p>He wrote several books, including <i>The Social Order</i>, <i>Power and Progress: Essays on Sociological Theory</i> and <i>American Sociological Theory</i> and has published many papers and essays in several sociological, anthropological, and literary journals.\n</p><p>He died on September 8, 1998 at Martha Jefferson Hospital in <a href=\"/wiki/Charlottesville,_Virginia\" title=\"Charlottesville, Virginia\">Charlottesville, Virginia</a> at 85.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Books\">Books</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robert_Bierstedt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Books\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <span class=\"citation book\">Durkheim, Emile; Bierstedt, Robert (1969). <i>Emile Durkheim: Selections from His Works Together with a Brief Biography by Robert Bierstedt</i>. Orion. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-297-17985-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-297-17985-3\">0-297-17985-3</a>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Bierstedt&amp;rft.au=Bierstedt%2C+Robert&amp;rft.au=Durkheim%2C+Emile&amp;rft.aufirst=Emile&amp;rft.aulast=Durkheim&amp;rft.btitle=Emile+Durkheim%3A+Selections+from+His+Works+Together+with+a+Brief+Biography+by+Robert+Bierstedt&amp;rft.date=1969&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=0-297-17985-3&amp;rft.pub=Orion&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"citation book\">Znaniecki, Florian (1969).  Robert Bierstedt, ed. <i>On Humanistic Sociology: Selected Papers</i>. University of Chicago Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-226-98842-2\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-226-98842-2\">0-226-98842-2</a>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Bierstedt&amp;rft.aulast=Znaniecki%2C+Florian&amp;rft.au=Znaniecki%2C+Florian&amp;rft.btitle=On+Humanistic+Sociology%3A+Selected+Papers&amp;rft.date=1969&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=0-226-98842-2&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Chicago+Press&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li> <span class=\"citation book\">Bierstedt, Robert (1974). <i>Power and Progress: Essays on Sociological Theory</i>. McGraw-Hill. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-07-005230-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-07-005230-1\">0-07-005230-1</a>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Bierstedt&amp;rft.au=Bierstedt%2C+Robert&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Bierstedt&amp;rft.btitle=Power+and+Progress%3A+Essays+on+Sociological+Theory&amp;rft.date=1974&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=0-07-005230-1&amp;rft.pub=McGraw-Hill&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li> <span class=\"citation book\">Bierstedt, Robert (1974). <i>The Social Order</i>. McGraw-Hill Education. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-07-005248-4\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-07-005248-4\">0-07-005248-4</a>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Bierstedt&amp;rft.au=Bierstedt%2C+Robert&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Bierstedt&amp;rft.btitle=The+Social+Order&amp;rft.date=1974&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=0-07-005248-4&amp;rft.pub=McGraw-Hill+Education&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"citation book\">Znaniecki, Florian (1980).  Robert Bierstedt, ed. <i>Cultural Sciences: Their Origin and Development</i>. Transaction. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-87855-689-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-87855-689-3\">0-87855-689-3</a>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Bierstedt&amp;rft.aulast=Znaniecki%2C+Florian&amp;rft.au=Znaniecki%2C+Florian&amp;rft.btitle=Cultural+Sciences%3A+Their+Origin+and+Development&amp;rft.date=1980&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=0-87855-689-3&amp;rft.pub=Transaction&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li> <span class=\"citation book\">Bierstedt, Robert (1981). <i>American Sociological Theory: A Critical History</i>. Academic Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-12-097482-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-12-097482-7\">0-12-097482-7</a>.</span><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARobert+Bierstedt&amp;rft.au=Bierstedt%2C+Robert&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.aulast=Bierstedt&amp;rft.btitle=American+Sociological+Theory%3A+A+Critical+History&amp;rft.date=1981&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.isbn=0-12-097482-7&amp;rft.pub=Academic+Press&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Robert_Bierstedt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><span class=\"citation news\">Williams, Monte (17 September 1998). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/1998/09/17/us/robert-bierstedt-85-sociologist-interested-in-constitutional-law.html\">\"Robert Bierstedt, 85, Sociologist Interested in Constitutional Law\"</a>. <i>New York Times</i><span class=\"reference-accessd